define ptr @test(i1 %c, ptr %a, ptr %b) {
  %sel = select i1 %c, ptr %a, ptr %b
  %gep = call ptr (ptr, ...) @llvm.structured.gep.p0(ptr elementtype(i32) %sel)
  ret ptr %gep
}

declare ptr @llvm.structured.gep.p0(ptr, ...) #0
attributes #0 = { nocallback nofree nosync nounwind speculatable willreturn memory(none) }
```","thoughts":"Let's try the select case. If InstCombine simplifies the select, it might trigger the bug. Wait, the previous one simplified to `%phi` directly. Why? Because `InstCombine` calls `InstSimplify` on the instruction first! `InstSimplify` sees `gep(%phi)` and simplifies it to `%phi` directly because `gep` with 0 indices simplifies to its operand. So `simplifyInstructionWithOperands` is NOT called!"}

